<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKERS LOSE LAST EXHIBITION TO JAZZ, 99-88 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Karl Malone scored 19 points and Felton Spencer and John Stockton had 13 in 
Utah's 99-88 exhibition victory over the Lakers on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Cedric Ceballos led the Lakers (5-3) with 26 points, 12 rebounds and four 
steals in their final exhibition.Rookie Eddie Jones added 19 points and Nick 
Van Exel had 12. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jazz (6-1) also got 11 points from Tom Chambers and 10 from John Crotty. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah led, 45-38, at halftime and increased its lead to 60-44 with 6:23 left in 
the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lakers went on an 18-3 run, with Ceballos scoring eight of the points, and 
cut the lead to 63-62 with 3:05 left in the third. Jones had a three-pointer 
and two foul shots at the end of the run. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jazz then outscored the Lakers, 34-17, taking its biggest lead at 97-79 
with 3:44 to play after Walter Bond's dunk off a pass from Bryon Russell. 
</P>
