<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARAMENDI COULD SAVE 20TH CENTURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Garamendi and the California Department of Insurance are doing all they 
can to get rid of 20th Century Insurance Co. because the insurer has charged 
too little for its policies and made too much money. 
</P>
<P>
 With careful underwriting and low-cost distribution, 20th Century has been 
able to offer some of the lowest-priced automobile insurance in 
California.Because of its efficiency, 20th Century has been able to earn more 
profit for each dollar of automobile premium than many of its less-efficient 
competitors. 
</P>
<P>
 By requiring 20th Century to return $119 million to its policyholders, 
Garamendi is leveling a gun on a company that is already reeling from 
earthquake losses ("20th Century's Quake Tab Hits $815 Million," Sept. 9). 
</P>
<P>
 John Garamendi might be able to save one of our state's best auto insurers by 
reducing or waiving the rebates. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN FORTMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 
</P>
<P>
 Fortman is an independent insurance agent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
