<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; SPORTS ITEMS AUCTION TO BENEFIT TEEN SHELTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angels pitching coach and baseball Hall of Fame candidate Bert Blyleven will 
serve as chairman of a silent sports memorabilia auction to support Laurel 
House, a local teen shelter. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raiser will be from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday, at Tustin 
Presbyterian Church, 225 W. Main St. 
</P>
<P>
 Featured at the auction will be autographed bats and baseballs, tickets to 
sporting events and items donated by sports stars such as Muhammad Ali, Richard 
Petty and Michael Chang. There will also be a raffle, live music and children's 
games, along with food and refreshment sales. Admission is free. 
</P>
<P>
 Gil J. Gonzales, who serves as a volunteer house parent at the nonprofit 
shelter, is coordinating the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Founded in 1986, Laurel House is a five-bedroom home that provides emergency 
shelter to runaway teen-agers. Counselors attempt to reunite the teens with 
their families. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional information is available by calling Laurel House at (714) 832-0207. 
ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
