<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California had its own North versus South civil war in the 1880s when 
residents of what is today Orange County fought to secede from Los Angeles 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 Though bloodless, this civil war was spirited, according to the book "A 
Hundred Years of Yesterdays." 
</P>
<P>
 Locals had many reasons for wanting their own county. The two often cited in 
history books: 
</P>
<P>
 * It cost $6 to take the stagecoach from Anaheim to the county seat in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 * The county's only rolled fire hose was kept in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 After much debate and pressure, Orange County was born in 1889. Today 
</P>
<P>
 P. J. O'Rourke, the conservative humorist and political pundit, will give a 
talk this morning at the Richard Nixon Library & Birthplace in Yorba Linda. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Rourke is a best-selling author of several books about politics and is often 
a panelist on Sunday morning news shows. He will offer his take on current 
events during the speech at 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The library is at 18001 Yorba Linda Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 993-5075. 
</P>
</TEXT>
