<TEXT>
<P>
 Chevron Wins Pension Ruling: A federal appeals court ruled that 44,000 former 
Gulf Oil Co. workers are not entitled to the money that existed in a pension 
plan when Gulf was purchased by Chevron Corp. in 1984. The U.S. 5th Circuit 
Court of Appeals in New Orleans found that nothing in federal law or the Gulf 
pension plan prohibited Chevron from merging the fund into its own pension plan 
in 1986. The former Gulf employees had claimed they were owed the surplus 
assets, estimated at more than $600 million, that had accumulated before the 
plans were combined. 
