<P>
 AST Posts Loss: As expected, AST Research Inc. announced a fiscal 
first-quarter loss of $39.9 million on revenue of $495.4 million.That contrasts 
with a profit of $8.2 million on revenue of $514.4 million recorded for the 
same period a year ago. Company officials blamed the loss on development and 
production delays and competitive pricing by rivals Compaq and IBM. Along with 
a management restructuring that is under way, Chief Executive Safi Qureshey 
said, the Irvine-based company will try to halve the number of models it sells 
in order to help cut production costs and streamline its marketing operations. 
The company recently announced the layoff of about 500 employees in Orange 
County and the resignations of several key executives. 
