</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Money Supply Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board said the measure known as M2 
rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,597.2 billion from a revised $3,593.4 billion 
for the week ended Oct. 17.An even broader measure, M3, rose to a seasonally 
adjusted $4,260.9 billion from a revised $4,256.7 billion. The narrowest supply 
measure, M1, was unchanged at $1,149.4 billion. M1 includes cash in 
circulation, deposits in checking accounts and non-bank traveler's checks. M2 
is M1 plus accounts such as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. M3 
is M2 plus less-liquid accounts such as large certificates of deposit. 
</P>
