<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vibrating Video: The Aura Interactor, a product used by deaf people to 
experience the physical sensations of sound, can now take video game players 
into a new dimension: inside the game itself to feel every tackle, laser blast 
or slam dunk.The Interactor, designed by Aura Systems of El Segundo, is a vest 
that can be plugged into the audio output of any gaming system to let players 
feel the vibrations of video games, music or home movies.  
</P>
<P>
 It includes a set of sensor controls for filtering certain sounds and 
adjusting the intensity of the vibrations. The Interactor has a suggested 
retail price of about $99. 
</P>
</TEXT>
