<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORUM TO FOCUS ON CONGRESSIONAL RACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A congressional candidates forum will take place Saturday at Rancho Santiago 
College in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum is sponsored by the college's political science department, the 
Concord Coalition of Orange County and United We Stand America's Orange County 
Chapter. 
</P>
<P>
 The coalition is a national, nonprofit, nonpartisan group dedicated to 
eliminating the federal budget deficit.  
</P>
<P>
 According to the coalition, the panelists will include some incumbents and 
challengers in Orange County's congressional races. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum will begin at 10 a.m. at Phillips Hall. 
</P>
