<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: BURLINGTON AIR EXPRESS PROFITS UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burlington Air Express, an Irvine-based subsidiary of Pittston Co., reported 
third-quarter operating profit of $22.2 million, 47% higher than the $15.1 
million recorded for the same quarter in 1993.Revenue increased 22% to $311.9 
million from $254.8 million. Year-to-date operating profit more than doubled to 
$52 million from $24.6 million for the comparable period of 1993. Nine-month 
revenue rose 21% to $875.7 million from $726 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102894-0185 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 093030 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 28, 1994, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
