<P>
THE SIMPSON CASE: A DAILY UPDATE; TRIAL HIGHLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A look at some of the key events in the O.J. Simpson murder trial on Thursday: 
</P>
<P>
 * Summary: After an unusually acerbic session between a prosecutor and a 
prospective jurors, defense attorneys accused prosecutors of treating black 
jury candidates differently than others. Government lawyers dismissed that 
charge as public relations work by the defense and said they were treating 
prospective jurors fairly. 
</P>
<P>
 * Court action: Superior Court Judge Lance A. Ito heard arguments in the 
defense's latest attack on evidence seized from Simpson's Ford Bronco, which 
was burglarized while in police custody. Ito did not rule, however. 
</P>
<P>
 * Outside the court: A lawyer for Simpson warned that any attempt to 
distribute purloined copies of a videotape of Simpson's 1985 marriage to Nicole 
Simpson will be met be a lawsuit. "Such an act, in addition to being illegal . 
. . is also morally offensive, repugnant and irresponsible," said Anthony 
Michael Glassman, a lawyer for Simpson. 
</P>
