<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: NORTHRIDGE; CSUN SLATES QUAKE RECOVERY JOB FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge will hold an Earthquake Recovery Job Fair and Minority 
Business Opportunity Day on campus Saturday to inform contracting businesses 
run by minorities and women how to procure jobs with private industries and 
public agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will offer a forum on how to find these jobs, as well. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting at 10 a.m. and ending at 4 p.m., workshops and panel discussions are 
scheduled on finance and bonding and the procurement of contracting work 
targeted at minorities and women in architecture, engineering, general 
contracting and painting, said Jeffrey Flores, outreach director of the 
Construction Management and Technical Service, a minority-owned management 
firm. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction Management oversees the rebuilding efforts at CSUN and all other 
construction projects at Cal State schools, Flores said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair and opportunity day are free and sponsored by Construction Management 
and Mayor Richard Riordan's office. Information: (818) 407-7717. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
