<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN CONVICTED OF KILLING EX-GIRLFRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Orange County Superior Court jury convicted a Brea man Thursday of 
first-degree murder for killing a former girlfriend who had told police he was 
involved in criminal activities, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Claude, 22, who was linked to the killing in part by DNA evidence, 
faces up to life in prison when he is sentenced Nov. 23, said Deputy Dist. 
Atty.Patrick K. Donahue. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancy Elsayed, 19, also of Brea, was shot to death in June, 1992, and found 
slumped over the steering wheel of a friend's car. The vehicle was parked at 
Savi Ranch Industrial Park near Auto Plaza Circle in Yorba Linda. 
</P>
<P>
 The prosecutor said that Claude was involved in auto thefts before the 
killing. Evidence presented at the trial indicated Claude might have killed his 
former girlfriend in part because she gave authorities information about Claude 
when she was detained during an investigation, Donahue said. 
</P>
<P>
 DNA testing showed Claude and Elsayed were sexually intimate shortly before 
the killing, evidence that helped link him to the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 Claude's defense attorney could not be reached for comment late Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
